<div class="container"><aside id="text-3" class="widget widget_text"><h2 class="widget-title">About Maeser</h2>			<div class="textwidget">
<p>Being part of the PRIDE isn't just about wearing a uniform and showing up to class.  Maeser is a holistic academic community that is more about giving your heart and soul to something that is truly meaningful.  Our Board, Administration, Faculty, and Staff love what they do and are dedicated to providing a quality classical, liberal arts education that prepares our students for Life!  </p>
<p>Maeser's mission is to "empower and inspire students to think critically, learn continually, and communicate effectively through use of the Socratic method to better themselves and their community."  We are a public charter school (7th - 12th grades) which means we embrace the State requirements, but as a charter we add our Maeser attributes of Truth, Honor, and Virtue to the core for a truly inspiring educational experience.  </p>
<p>We welcome you to come take a tour, listen to a Socratic Seminar, or participate in a service opportunity.  Maeser is a wonderful place to go to school, work, or volunteer.  Don't just take our word for it, but come experience it for yourself!  You'll soon see why the Lions have Pride!</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br>
Robyn Ellis, Director</p>
</div>
